Rating: 3
Delicious, easy to make and perfect for Thanksgiving. My husband made this and forgot the raisins, but it was still great. I'd add fresh cranberries to offset the sweet of the apples and to add color, dried cranberries would also work but would add another sugar which isn't needed with the wonderful sweet apples. We used two round sourdough loaves so upped the recipe a bit, just estimated measurements for apples, celery and bread - it was great and made two 13x9 pans. We'll definitely make this again, and again.

